article.headline: William & Mary 60, Drexel 47
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Laimis Kisielius scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds -- including three rebounds in the last two minutes as Drexel attempted a comeback -- as William and Mary held on to beat the Dragons 60-47 on Wednesday night. The Tribe (15-11, 8-8 Colonial Athletic Association) saw a comfortable 13-point lead dwindle in the last six minutes of the game, as Drexel used a 13-4 run to pull to with four with 2:23 remaining. But the Dragons (19-7, 11-5) couldn't score again, and William and Mary padded their margin in the closing minutes with steady free throw shooting. Adam Payton scored 13 points for the Tribe and Nathan Mann added 12. The Dragons' Frank Elegar scored 18 and Chaz Crawford had 10.
